entry__2\">\n Image (glyph)\n </td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"aww1665702586248__table_d11126e1_d11127e1_d11128e1__entry__1\">\n I&amp;\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"aww1665702586248__table_d11126e1_d11127e1_d11128e1__entry__2\">\n Image (URL)\n </td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"aww1665702586248__table_d11126e1_d11127e1_d11128e1__entry__1\">\n LD\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"aww1665702586248__table_d11126e1_d11127e1_d11128e1__entry__2\">\n Linear date\n </td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"aww1665702586248__table_d11126e1_d11127e1_d11128e1__entry__1\">\n LT\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"aww1665702586248__table_d11126e1_d11127e1_d11128e1__entry__2\">\n Linear time\n </td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"aww1665702586248__table_d11126e1_d11127e1_d11128e1__entry__1\">\n LE\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"aww1665702586248__table_d11126e1_d11127e1_d11128e1__entry__2\">\n Linear date and time\n </td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"aww1665702586248__table_d11126e1_d11127e1_d11128e1__entry__1\">\n H\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"aww1665702586248__table_d11126e1_d11127e1_d11128e1__entry__2\">\n Handle\n </td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"aww1665702586248__table_d11126e1_d11127e1_d11128e1__entry__1\">\n XM\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"aww1665702586248__table_d11126e1_d11127e1_d11128e1__entry__2\">\n XMLStream\n </td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"aww1665702586248__table_d11126e1_d11127e1_d11128e1__entry__1\">\n SREF\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"aww1665702586248__table_d11126e1_d11127e1_d11128e1__entry__2\">\n Struct By Reference\n </td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"aww1665702586248__table_d11126e1_d11127e1_d11128e1__entry__1\">\n SVAL\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"aww1665702586248__table_d11126e1_d11127e1_d11128e1__entry__2\">\n Struct By Value\n </td>\n</tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"dataTables_scrollFoot\" style=\"overflow: hidden; border: 0px; width: 100%;\"><div class=\"dataTables_scrollFootInner\"><table class=\"table dataTable no-footer\" count-columns=\"2\" style=\"margin-left: 0px;\"><tfoot></tfoot></table></div></div></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"aww1665702586248__section_svv_ydg_pwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d832547e271\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"aww1665702586248__p_d98048e1_d98049e1_d98050e1\">The default value of a field is determined by the\n            template used to create the field. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"osd1692183897129.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/osd1692183897129.html\" title=\"Templates are development objects that are copied during development to create new objects. Uniface provides an extensive set of default templates, but you can also create your own.\">Templates and Palettes</a>. In most cases, the default data type is string.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"aww1665702586248__section_vwt_zdg_pwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d832547e287\">Data Type <code class=\"ph codeph\">Any</code> for Component Variables</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"aww1665702586248__p_d98054e1_d98055e1_d98056e1\">For component variables, it is also possible to select\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">$</code> (Any) in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Data Type</span> field. This\n            indicates that the data type is determined by the source data that you assign to the\n            variable.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"aww1665702586248__p_d98057e1_d98058e1_d98059e1\">You cannot use a <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Display Format</span>\n            with the Any data type.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"aww1665702586248__section_nhz_b2g_pwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d832547e311\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"aww1665702586248__ul_hwn_d2g_pwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"aww1665702586248__li_d39707e1_d39708e1_d39709e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lym1665702585074.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lym1665702585074.html\" title=\"A Field is a Development Object that represents a unit of data in an Entity. This could represent a column in a DBMS table or data that is not stored in the database, such as a derived field or a user interface control. Its associated properties define the way it is stored, its GUI representation, and default behavior.\">Field</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"aww1665702586248__li_d39710e1_d39711e1_d39712e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zyw1705402059478.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zyw1705402059478.html\" title=\"Component variables are temporary, named data storage areas for a component. They are available to all ProcScript in the component.\">Component Variables</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"aww1665702586248__li_d39713e1_d39714e1_d39715e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"luz1665702709079.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/luz1665702709079.html\" title=\"A Global Variable is a Development Object that defines a typed variable that can be accessed by all ProcScript in the application.\">Global Variable</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eqt1665702682684.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ProcScript: Data Types</a><p>Data types define the characteristics of the data and determine how Uniface handles the data during processing and storage. They are specified for parameters, variables, and return values in ProcScript, as well as for fields, global variables, and component variables.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612017\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612017\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Data Type Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Data Type Uniface data type to use for this field, variable, or parameter. The default value is S (String). Search: Column Value Representation Filter results... 20 rows found Export to Excel Export to CSV Value Representation Filter 20 rows found Filter 20 rows found Value Representation S String R Raw data N Numeric F Floating decimal point D Date T Time E Combined date and time B Boolean I Image (any source) I# Image (database) I@ Image (disk file) I^ Image (glyph) I& Image (URL) LD Linear date LT Linear time LE Linear date and time H Handle XM XMLStream SREF Struct By Reference SVAL Struct By Value Description The default value of a field is determined by the template used to create the field. For more information, see Templates and Palettes . In most cases, the default data type is string. Data Type Any for Component Variables For component variables, it is also possible to select $ (Any) in the Data Type field. This indicates that the data type is determined by the source data that you assign to the variable. You cannot use a Display Format with the Any data type. Applies To Field Component Variables Global Variable Related Links ProcScript: Data Types Data types define the characteristics of the data and determine how Uniface handles the data during processing and storage. They are specified for parameters, variables, and return values in ProcScript, as well as for fields, global variables, and component variables. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}